WITH
LKP_WC_REPORT_HISTORY AS (
	SELECT
	WRH_REPORTED_DATE,
	WRH_CLAIM_NBR,
	WRH_OBJECT_SEQ_NBR,
	WRH_CLIENT_ID,
	WRH_REPORT_TYPE
	FROM (
		SELECT WC_REPORT_HISTORY_STAGE.WRH_REPORTED_DATE as WRH_REPORTED_DATE, WC_REPORT_HISTORY_STAGE.WRH_CLAIM_NBR as WRH_CLAIM_NBR, WC_REPORT_HISTORY_STAGE.WRH_OBJECT_SEQ_NBR as WRH_OBJECT_SEQ_NBR, WC_REPORT_HISTORY_STAGE.WRH_CLIENT_ID as WRH_CLIENT_ID, LTRIM(RTRIM(WC_REPORT_HISTORY_STAGE.WRH_REPORT_TYPE)) as WRH_REPORT_TYPE FROM WC_REPORT_HISTORY_STAGE
	)
	QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY WRH_CLAIM_NBR,WRH_OBJECT_SEQ_NBR,WRH_CLIENT_ID,WRH_REPORT_TYPE ORDER BY WRH_REPORTED_DATE) = 1
),
LKP_CLAIM_COVERAGE AS (
	SELECT
	CVR_INSD_TYPE_CD,
	CVR_CLAIM_NBR
	FROM (
		SELECT 
		A.CVR_INSD_TYPE_CD as CVR_INSD_TYPE_CD, 
		LTRIM(RTRIM(A.CVR_CLAIM_NBR)) as CVR_CLAIM_NBR 
		FROM 
		@{pipeline().parameters.SOURCE_TABLE_OWNER}.CLAIM_COVERAGE_STAGE A
	)
	QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY CVR_CLAIM_NBR ORDER BY CVR_INSD_TYPE_CD) = 1
),
LKP_CLM_COMMENTS AS (
	SELECT
	TCC_COMMENT_TXT,
	FOLDER_KEY,
	COMMENT_ITEM_NBR
	FROM (
		SELECT A.TCC_COMMENT_TXT as TCC_COMMENT_TXT, 
		A.FOLDER_KEY as FOLDER_KEY, A.COMMENT_ITEM_NBR as COMMENT_ITEM_NBR FROM CLM_COMMENTS_STAGE A
		INNER JOIN WORKERS_CPS_LOSS_STAGE B
		ON A.FOLDER_KEY = B.CWC_CLAIM_NBR
	)
	QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY FOLDER_KEY,COMMENT_ITEM_NBR ORDER BY TCC_COMMENT_TXT) = 1

		LTRIM(RTRIM(CO.claim_occurrence_key)) as claimant_num, 
		LTRIM(RTRIM(CP.claim_party_key)) as claim_party_role_code

		@{pipeline().parameters.TARGET_TABLE_OWNER}.claim_party CP,

SQ_workers_comp_claimant_detail AS (
	SELECT a.wc_claimant_det_id, a.wc_claimant_det_ak_id, a.eff_from_date, a.eff_to_date 
	FROM
	 @{pipeline().parameters.TARGET_TABLE_OWNER}.workers_comp_claimant_detail a
	WHERE EXISTS(SELECT 1			
			FROM  @{pipeline().parameters.TARGET_TABLE_OWNER}.workers_comp_claimant_detail b
			WHERE b.source_sys_id = '@{pipeline().parameters.SOURCE_SYSTEM_ID}'  AND b.crrnt_snpsht_flag = 1
			AND a.wc_claimant_det_ak_id = b.wc_claimant_det_ak_id
			GROUP BY wc_claimant_det_ak_id
			HAVING COUNT(*) > 1)
	ORDER BY wc_claimant_det_ak_id, eff_from_date  DESC
),
EXP_Lag_eff_from_date1 AS (
	SELECT
	wc_claimant_detail_id,
	wc_claimant_det_ak_id,
	eff_from_date,
	eff_to_date AS orig_eff_to_date,
	-- *INF*: IIF(wc_claimant_det_ak_id = v_PREV_ROW_wc_claimant_det_ak_id, ADD_TO_DATE(v_PREV_ROW_eff_from_date,'SS',-1),orig_eff_to_date)
	IFF(wc_claimant_det_ak_id = v_PREV_ROW_wc_claimant_det_ak_id, ADD_TO_DATE(v_PREV_ROW_eff_from_date, 'SS', - 1), orig_eff_to_date) AS v_eff_to_date,
	v_eff_to_date AS eff_to_date,
	eff_from_date AS v_PREV_ROW_eff_from_date,
	wc_claimant_det_ak_id AS v_PREV_ROW_wc_claimant_det_ak_id,
	SYSDATE AS modified_date,
	0 AS crrnt_snpsht_flag
	FROM SQ_workers_comp_claimant_detail
),
FIL_FirstRowInAKGroup AS (
	SELECT
	wc_claimant_detail_id, 
	orig_eff_to_date, 
	eff_to_date, 
	modified_date, 
	crrnt_snpsht_flag
	FROM EXP_Lag_eff_from_date1
	WHERE orig_eff_to_date <> eff_to_date

--If these two dates equal each other we are dealing with the first row in an AK group.  This row
--does not need to be expired or updated for any reason thus it can be filtered out
-- but we must source it to capture the eff_from_date of this row 
--so that we can properly expire the subsequent row
),
UPD_workers_comp_claimant_detail AS (
	SELECT
	wc_claimant_detail_id, 
	eff_to_date, 
	modified_date, 
	crrnt_snpsht_flag
	FROM FIL_FirstRowInAKGroup
),
workers_comp_claimant_detail_update AS (
	MERGE INTO @{pipeline().parameters.TARGET_TABLE_OWNER}.workers_comp_claimant_detail AS T
	USING UPD_workers_comp_claimant_detail AS S
	ON T.wc_claimant_det_id = S.wc_claimant_detail_id
	WHEN MATCHED BY TARGET THEN
	UPDATE SET T.crrnt_snpsht_flag = S.crrnt_snpsht_flag, T.eff_to_date = S.eff_to_date, T.modified_date = S.modified_date
),
